str2: To change my place (abode), leave, depart, remove, pass over. From meta and the base of basis; to change place.
Thence, from that place. From ekei; thence.
Of Hebrew origin; Jesus, the name of our Lord and two other Israelites.

str2: Gen: from; dat: beside, in the presence of; acc: alongside of.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Probably prolonged from hals; the sea.
Of Hebrew origin; Galiloea, a region of Palestine.

str2: To go up, mount, ascend; of things: I rise, spring up, come up. From ana and the base of basis; to go up.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
A mountain, hill. Probably from an obsolete oro; a mountain: -hill, mount(-ain).

str2: To sit, be seated, enthroned; I dwell, reside. From kata; and hemai; to sit down; figuratively, to remain, reside.
(a) there, yonder, in that place, (b) thither, there. Of uncertain affinity; there; by extension, thither.
